The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science that falls under several sub-categories. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with the complexity of computing problems. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as communication complexity is often used to analyze algorithms. cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper defines a new complexity measure. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as communication complexity has applications in machine learning. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also possible as communication complexity involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic techniques.
